Aim
To gather information about domains and IP addresses using Robtex and analyze ASN details, hosting provider
information, and reverse DNS records.
Introduction
Robtex is an online network intelligence and reconnaissance tool used to collect information about domains,
IP addresses, DNS records, Autonomous System Numbers (ASN), and hosting providers.
It is widely used in cybersecurity and digital forensics for network investigation and information gathering.
Procedure
Step 1: Open Robtex Website
Open a web browser and visit:
Robtex Official Website
Step 2: Enter Target Domain
In the search box, enter the target domain:
www.grace.edu.in
Step 3: Start Investigation
Click the search button to begin information gathering.
Step 4: Analyze Information
Observe the following details:
• IP address
• DNS records
• ASN details
• Hosting provider
• Reverse DNS information
Implementation
Target Domain
www.grace.edu.in
Information Collected
